  "soap_summary": "19-year-old female (Jessica Smith) with 3-day history of burning/stinging on urination (dysuria) and crampy lower abdominal pain. Reports a little blood in urine earlier today and foul-smelling urine. Denies fever, back/flank pain, nausea/vomiting, increased urinary frequency, or diarrhea. Past history notable for irritable bowel syndrome. Allergic to clindamycin (swelling). Tried OTC ibuprofen a few days ago without benefit. Physician considers a probable simple urinary tract infection and plans to prescribe antibiotics (nitrofurantoin or trimethoprim, typically 3 days twice daily). Advised fluids, cranberry, avoid sex while symptomatic, pregnancy test if not improving, and to return/call if worsening or signs of systemic infection.",
